{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T04:25:42.718Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on the official Claude Cookbook documentation and Anthropic's \"Building Effective Agents\" research, "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Orchestrator-Workers\""},{"type":"text","text":" is an "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"orchestration pattern where a central LLM dynamically breaks down complex tasks, delegates them to specialized worker LLMs, and synthesizes their results"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What It Is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The orchestrator-workers pattern has a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"central orchestrator LLM"},{"type":"text","text":" that analyzes each unique task and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"dynamically determines the best subtasks"},{"type":"text","text":", then delegates to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"worker LLMs"},{"type":"text","text":" that execute those subtasks, with the orchestrator merging results at the end."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Basic Flow"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"User Task → Orchestrator (central LLM)\n         ↓\n   [Task Decomposition]\n         ↓\n  Subtask 1 │ Subtask 2 │ Subtask 3\nWorker 1    │ Worker 2    │ Worker 3\n    ↓       │     ↓       │    ↓\n  Result 1  │  Result 2   │ Result 3\n         ↓\n[Orchestrator Synthesizes Results]\n         ↓\n    Final Output"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Components"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Component"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Role"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Characteristics"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Orchestrator"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Central LLM that decomposes work"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Analyzes task, determines subtasks, merges results"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Workers"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Specialized LLMs executing subtasks"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Execute assigned subtasks, return results"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Interfaces"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Contracts between steps"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Define inputs/outputs between orchestrator and workers"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How It Works"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The pattern follows a clear sequence:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Task arrives"},{"type":"text","text":" — User submits a complex task to orchestrator"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Orchestrator decomposes"},{"type":"text","text":" — Orchestrator analyzes task and breaks into 2-3 subtasks with different approaches"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Workers execute"},{"type":"text","text":" — Each subtask is sent to a worker LLM with specialized prompt"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Results collected"},{"type":"text","text":" — All worker outputs are gathered"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Orchestrator synthesizes"},{"type":"text","text":" — Orchestrator merges results into final output"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example: Product Description"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Original task: \"Write product description for eco-friendly water bottle\"\n- Orchestrator creates 2-3 approaches (different styles: technical, marketing, sustainability-focused)\n- Each worker generates content based on their style guidelines\n- Orchestrator combines all results into final polished description"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What to Focus On"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"When implementing orchestrator-workers, focus on these critical aspects:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Aspect"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why It's Important"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Task decomposition"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"What belongs in the orchestrator vs workers? Orchestrator does decomposition; workers do execution"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Interfaces as contracts"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Define explicit inputs/outputs between orchestrator and workers"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Evaluation gates"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Where to add review/evaluation between steps?"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"When to Use This Workflow"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The orchestrator-workers pattern is ideal when:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Condition"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why It Helps"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Subtasks are unpredictable"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You can't know all required subtasks before starting — orchestrator discovers them dynamically"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Complex tasks"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Task complexity exceeds single LLM's reasoning depth"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Need dynamic decomposition"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Subtasks emerge as you investigate (e.g., research agents)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Multiple perspectives needed"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Want different approaches/styles for same task"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Parallel execution beneficial"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Workers can run independently without dependency"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Research system example"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Research task: \"Investigate climate impact of agriculture\"\n- Start: Orchestrator doesn't know all subtopics yet\n- Workers: Parallel research on different angles (soil, livestock, transportation)\n- Orchestrator: Reviews results, identifies new subtopics discovered, assigns more research\n- Loop: Continues until comprehensive coverage"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"orchestrator-workers pattern's unique capability"},{"type":"text","text":" — orchestrator can revise task decomposition based on what workers discover."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Orchestrator-Workers vs. Parallelization"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Aspect"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Orchestrator-Workers"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Parallelization"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Task breakdown"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Orchestrator dynamically determines subtasks"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pre-defined, static subtasks"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Adaptability"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Orchestrator can revise decomposition mid-process"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All subtasks run once, no revision"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use case"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Subtasks unpredictable, complex tasks"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Subtasks independent and known upfront"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Flexibility"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"High — orchestrator adapts based on results"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Low — fixed parallel structure"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key difference"},{"type":"text","text":": Parallelization breaks a task into fixed subtasks upfront. Orchestrator-workers has the orchestrator "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"analyze each unique task and dynamically determine the best subtasks"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation Best Practices"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Use XML for Structured Output"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Claude excels at XML, so define interfaces using XML tags:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"xml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<task>\n  <type>analysis</type>\n  <description>Analyze security vulnerabilities</description>\n</task>"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. Pass Original Task to Workers"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Workers should receive both the subtask AND the original task context:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Original task: \"Write product description...\"\nSubtask: \"Generate content based on Technical Style Guidelines\""}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. Add Evaluation Gates"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Insert review steps between orchestrator and workers to validate quality:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Worker → Evaluation Gate → Orchestrator (if passes) → Synthesize\n                            ↓ (if fails)\n                        Retry Worker"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"4. Use Turn-Based Execution (Optional)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For complex tasks, use turn-based pattern where orchestrator revises after each worker wave:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Wave 1: Orchestrator → Workers 1,2,3 → Results\nWave 2: Orchestrator (reviews results) → Workers 4,5 (new subtasks)\nWave 3: Orchestrator synthesizes → Final"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mental Model"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of orchestrator-workers like a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"project manager with specialized contractors"},{"type":"text","text":": the PM (orchestrator) analyzes the project, breaks it into phases, assigns each phase to specialized contractors (workers), reviews their work, and integrates everything into the final deliverable. The PM can adjust the plan if contractors discover new issues."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Orchestrator-workers: central LLM dynamically breaks down tasks, delegates to workers, synthesizes results"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Orchestrator analyzes each unique task and determines best subtasks dynamically"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Workers are specialized LLMs executing assigned subtasks"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best for: unpredictable subtasks, complex tasks, research systems, multi-perspective analysis"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Unique capability: orchestrator can revise decomposition based on what workers discover mid-process"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Focus on: task decomposition boundaries, interface contracts, evaluation gates"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use XML for structured inputs/outputs (Claude excels at XML)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pass original task context to workers for better alignment"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Different from parallelization: parallelization has fixed subtasks; orchestrator-workers is adaptive"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Can add evaluation gates between orchestrator and workers for quality control"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The pattern enables multi-agent research systems where orchestrator discovers subtopics through workers' research and assigns follow-up investigations dynamically."}]}]}}
